            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This bulletin presents an explanation, and the location, of the identification numbers found on
                    direct injection, and indirect injection, remanufactured engines. Examples of properly identified
                    connecting rod bearing journals, crankshaft main bearing journal diameter under size, and piston
                    bore diameter, identification marks, and remanufacture dates will be given.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The 7.3L IDIT (indirect injection turbocharged) engine and the 7.3L DIT (direct injection
                            turbocharged) engine are Ford products. They may, however, be serviced by International
                            dealers.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <svcproc svcproctype="idcomponent" graphiccount="0">
            <title>inDirect Injection Serial Number Stamping</title>
            <para>The serial number, connecting rod bearing journal, crankshaft main bearing journal diameter under
                size, and piston bore diameter, identification marks, and remanufacture dates, for remanufactured
                indirect injection engines are stamped behind the injection pump timing gear cover. The first and second
                row of numbers indicate the remanufactured-engine's serial number. The numbers (identification marks)
                located on the left side of the bottom row indicate the rod, main, and bore, sizes. The numbers located
                on the right side of the bottom row indicate the month and year during which the engine was
                remanufactured.
            </para>
            <para>
                <hotlnk xrefid="tsi011250" appearance="hottext">
                    <xref refid="tsi011250"/>
                </hotlnk>
                This illustration presents an engine that has the serial number B73128165. Its rod bearing journal
                undersize mark is 1, its main bearing journal undersize mark is also 1, and its bore oversize mark is 1.
                The remanufacture date, 5 01 or May 2001, follows the bore size.
                <hotlnk xrefid="tsi0189">
                    <xref refid="tsi0189"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for indirect injection engine rod, main, and bore, marking convention unit conversions.
            </para>
