        <svcproc>
            <title>direct Injection identification Number Stamping</title>
            <para>The serial number, connecting rod bearing journal, crankshaft main bearing journal diameter undersize,
                and piston bore diameter, sizes, and remanufacture dates, of each remanufactured direct injection engine
                are stamped on the engine's block, immediately to the rear of the oil cooler/oil filter header.
            </para>
            <para>The top row of numbers are the remanufactured-engine's serial number. The numbers located on the left
                side of the bottom row indicate the rod bearing journal identification nominal undersize, crankshaft
                main bearing journal diameter undersize, and bore nominal oversize diameter. The numbers located on the
                right side of the bottom row indicate the month and year during which the engine was remanufactured.
                <hotlnk xrefid="tsi011252">
                    <xref refid="tsi011252"/>
                </hotlnk>
                ;
                <hotlnk xrefid="tsi011251">
